    "updated_at": "2015-08-25T03:09:15Z",
    "body": "@Somiac I just came across another style I needed to add to make my app feel more native and thought you/others may be interested:\n\n``` css\na:not([draggable=true]), img:not([draggable=true]) {\n    -webkit-user-drag: none;\n    user-drag: none; /* Technically not supported in Electron yet */\n}\na[href^=\"http://\"],\na[href^=\"https://\"],\na[href^=\"ftp://\"] {\n    -webkit-user-drag: auto;\n    user-drag: auto; /* Technically not supported in Electron yet */\n}\n```\n\nDepending on your use-case, you may want to scope it to something like `a.button` instead.\n\nAlso note `draggable` is an [enumerated attribute, not a Boolean one](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Global_attributes/draggable), hence `=true` in the selector.\n\nUnfortunately `:local-link` was [removed from the Selectors Level 4 spec](http://css4.rocks/selectors-level-4/local-link-pseudo-class.php) so it looks like the `href` attribute \"hack\" will be there for a while. :-P\n"
